<TITLE> China commits 1,000 tonnes of rice </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 28 (bdnews24.com)  China has pledged 1,000 tons of rice for cyclone survivors, an army officer said Wednesday. At a news briefing in the evening, general staff officer Lieutenant Colonel Faruque Hossain said army relief efforts were continuing. He said the death toll rose to 3,256. As of Wednesday, some 1,227 tons of relief materials were distributed among survivors. Faruque said China pledged 1,000 tons of rice that he hoped would be sent soon and added that 10 countries have so far taken part in the relief efforts. France sent two water-purifying plants, while India sent 80 tons of rice, medicine, water filters, tents and blankets. Italy sent power generators, water tanks, blankets and kitchen utensils. Japan sent power generators, blankets, water tanks, tents and mattresses. Pakistan sent tents, rice, baby food, medicine, flying hospitals and Saudi Arabia sent 95 tons of relief material. The two water purifying plants sent by France were being installed in Patharghata and Sharankhola. bdnews2
